messages.message:
Do you think you guys will find this at all productive, https://instabase.slack.com/apps/AA16LBCH2-asana
The premise of it is the ability to quickly add tasks in asana from conversations happening here. So imagine if I said a message like, "why can't I right click on a ibflow file in instabase and have it auto run". You could right click on that comment and assign a ticket in asana automatically.

Let me know your thoughts.
